SIMPLE: strengthen
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strengthen
<hw>Strength"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Strengthened</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Strengthening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
make strong or stronger; to add strength to; <as>as, to
<ex>strengthen</ex> a limb, a bridge, an army; to <ex>strengthen</ex> an
obligation; to <ex>strengthen</ex> authority</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let noble Warwick, Cobham, and the rest, . . . ⟦br⟧
With powerful policy <qex>strengthen</qex> themselves.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To animate; to encourage; to fix in
resolution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Charge Joshua, and encourage him, and <qex>strengthen</qex>
him.</q> <rj><qau>Deut. iii. 28.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To invigorate; confirm; establish; fortify;
animate; encourage.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strengthen</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Strengthen
<hw>Strength"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To grow strong
or stronger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The young disease, that must subdue at length,⟦br⟧
Grows with his growth, and <qex>strengthens</qex> with his strength.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strengthener</ent>⟦br⟧
